    "The GBSO-TAENN improves the seizure detection scheme's overall performance by identifying original features and optimal hyper-parameters like dropout, decay, leaving and cosine similarity.",
    "These parameters are mainly considered for computing the loss function, which can be utilized for training the classifier with reduced computational complexity. 5.",
    "Moreover, the different EEG datasets, such as the University of Bonn and CHB-MIT, have been utilized to test the proposed scheme's effectiveness and accuracy during the experimental validation.",
    "These datasets comprise more complex cases of difficult signals to handle.",
    "The other sections of this paper are structuralized as follows: section \"Related works\" investigates the conventional EEG signal detection and classification techniques with their benefits and demerits."
